The paper discusses privacy risks associated with web payments via cryptocurrencies, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of third-party trackers and the linking of transactions on the blockchain, which could fall under the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CY), databases (cs.DB), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses mitigations for the privacy risks, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
